            {
              "id": "c9a327d6-7e1e-3673-9419-708610ca1a1d",
              "name": "Hardcoded Private Key Vulnerability Detected",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nHardcoded Private Key Vulnerability Detected is a security flaw that occurs when a developer hardcodes a private key in a software application. This is a serious vulnerability because if an attacker gains access to the source code, they can easily extract the private key and use it for malicious purposes such as decrypting sensitive data, impersonating the server, or even launching a man-in-the-middle attack.\n\nIn Python, this vulnerability can occur when a developer hardcodes a private RSA key directly into the source code, as shown in the provided code snippet.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, avoid hardcoding private keys directly into the source code. Instead, use secure methods to store and retrieve keys, such as environment variables, secure key vaults, or configuration files that are not included in the source code repository.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nInstead of hardcoding the private key, you can store it in an environment variable. Here's how you can do it:\n\n```python\nimport os\nprivate_key = os.getenv('PRIVATE_KEY')\n```\n\nIn this code, `PRIVATE_KEY` is the name of the environment variable that stores your private key. You can set this environment variable in your operating system, or in the configuration of your hosting environment.\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe provided code snippet does not include any library dependencies.\n\n## References\n\n- [CWE-798: Use of Hard-coded Credentials](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/798.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-798",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/798.html"
                  }
                ],
                "kind": "FAIL",
                "security-severity": "8.0",
                "tags": [
                  "security",
                  "CWE-798"
                ]
              }
